Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.10,0:00:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}早上好 还好吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Good morning. How are you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.22,0:00:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}很好吧 对不对{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}It's been great, hasn't it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.33,0:00:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我已经飘飘然了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I've been blown away by the whole thing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.77,0:00:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我要飘走了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}In fact, I'm leaving.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.12,0:00:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这次会议有三个主题 这三个主题贯穿会议始终{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}There have been three themes running through the conference{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}并且和 我要谈的内容有关{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}which are relevant to what I want to talk about.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.67,0:00:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}其中之一就是人类创造力的伟大例证 {\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}One is the extraordinary evidence of human creativity {\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.59,0:00:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这些例证已经体现在之前的演讲当中{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}in all of the presentations{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.30,0:00:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}以及在座各位的身上{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}that we've had and in all of the people here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.59,0:00:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}从这些例证中我们看到了创新的多样化 和多领域{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Just the variety of it and the range of it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.04,0:00:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}第二点 这些创新也让我们意识到 我们不知道未来会发生什么{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}The second is that it's put us in a place where we have no idea what's going to happen, in terms of the future.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.22,0:00:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}完全不知道 未来会如何{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}No idea how this may play out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.15,0:00:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我对教育感兴{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I have an interest in education.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.77,0:01:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}事实上 我发现每个人都对教育感兴趣{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Actually, what I find is everybody has an interest in education.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.29,0:01:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}难道不是吗?{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Don't you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.63,0:01:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我发现这很有趣{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I find this very interesting.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.40,0:01:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}如果你参加一个晚宴 你说 你在教育部门工作{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If you're at a dinner party, and you say you work in education --{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.85,0:01:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}坦白的讲 如果你在教育部门工作 事实上你不会经常参加晚宴{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Actually, you're not often at dinner parties, frankly.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.75,0:01:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}所以你不会被问及你是做哪行的{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If you work in education, you're not asked.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.30,0:01:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你永远不会被问到 很奇怪{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And you're never asked back, curiously. That's strange to me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.10,0:01:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但是如果你被问及 他们问 “你从事什么行业”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}But if you are, and you say to somebody, you know, they say, "What do you do?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.38,0:01:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你说你在教育部门工作 你会发现他们涨红了脸{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and you say you work in education, you can see the blood run from their face.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.07,0:01:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}那意思好像是 “我的天啊” “为什么让我碰上 {\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}They're like, "Oh my God," you know, "Why me? {\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.09,0:01:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}整整一周我才出来一次”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}My one night out all week."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.38,0:01:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但如果你要他们谈谈他们的受教育经历 他们会把你“钉到墙上”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}But if you ask about their education, they pin you to the wall.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.65,0:01:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}因为这些事情都涉及 个人的隐私,对吗?{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Because it's one of those things that goes deep with people, am I right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.78,0:01:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}比如宗教信仰,薪水等{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Like religion, and money and other things.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.47,0:01:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我对教育特别感兴趣 我认为我们都是如此{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}So I have a big interest in education, and I think we all do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.00,0:01:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我们对此有巨大的既得利益{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We have a huge vested interest in it,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.00,0:02:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}部分因为教育旨在 将我们带入我们无法掌握的未来{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}partly because it's education that's meant to take us into this future that we can't grasp.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.84,0:02:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}大家想想 今年入学的小孩 2065将退休{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If you think of it, children starting school this year will be retiring in 2065.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.32,0:02:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}没人知道会怎样 虽然过去四天会议进程里 都是关于这方面的专业讨论-{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Nobody has a clue, despite all the expertise that's been on parade for the past four days,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.56,0:02:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但我们还是无法预知这个世界 五年后的样子{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}what the world will look like in five years' time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.92,0:02:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这就是为何我们要让这些孩子 接受教育{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And yet we're meant to be educating them for it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.10,0:02:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我认为正是未来的不确定性 决定其非同寻常{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}So the unpredictability, I think, is extraordinary.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.66,0:02:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}第三点就是 我们都认同一个观点{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And the third part of this is that we've all agreed, nonetheless,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.24,0:02:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这些孩子的特别之处正是 他们的创新能力{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}on the really extraordinary capacities that children have -- their capacities for innovation.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.00,0:02:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我觉得昨晚 Sirena 的表现令人惊奇 对吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I mean, Sirena last night was a marvel, wasn't she? Just seeing what she could do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.47,0:02:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}她很出色 但是我认为 她在孩提时代时没显得与众不同{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And she's exceptional, but I think she's not, so to speak, exceptional in the whole of childhood.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.99,0:02:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}现在的教育提倡的是 一个有奉献精神的老师{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}What you have there is a person of extraordinary dedication{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.75,0:02:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}能发现一个天才学生{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}who found a talent.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.63,0:02:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但我认为 所有孩子都是伟大的天才{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And my contention is, all kids have tremendous talents.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.82,0:02:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}而我们却无情地扼杀了他们的才能{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And we squander them, pretty ruthlessly.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.07,0:03:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}所以我想谈谈教育和 创造力{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}So I want to talk about education and I want to talk about creativity.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.85,0:03:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我认为 创造力和文化知识在教育中占同样比重{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}My contention is that creativity now is as important in education as literacy,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.97,0:03:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}所以这两方面我们应同等对待{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and we should treat it with the same status.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.12,0:03:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}谢谢{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Thank you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.37,0:03:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}而且 非常感谢{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}That was it, by the way. Thank you very much.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.95,0:03:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}还剩15分钟{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}So, 15 minutes left.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.72,0:03:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我出生于 说错了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Well, I was born. No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.90,0:03:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}最近我听到一个很不错的故事 我很愿意讲讲这个故事{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I heard a great story recently -- I love telling it --{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.27,0:03:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}说的是一个小女孩正在上绘画课{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}of a little girl who was in a drawing lesson.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}小女孩只有六岁 她坐在教室的后排 正在画画{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}She was six, and she was at the back, drawing,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.80,0:03:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}而她的老师评价她几乎从不 注意听讲{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and the teacher said this girl hardly ever paid attention,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.15,0:03:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但在绘画课上她却听得很认真{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and in this drawing lesson, she did.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.10,0:03:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}老师饶有兴趣地走过去{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}The teacher was fascinated. She went over to her,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.87,0:03:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}问她：“你在画什么”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and she said, "What are you drawing?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.87,0:03:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}她说：“我画的是上帝”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And the girl said, "I'm drawing a picture of God."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.47,0:03:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}老师说：“可是没人知道上帝长什么样”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And the teacher said, "But nobody knows what God looks like."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.90,0:03:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这时小女孩说： “他们马上就能知道上帝的样子了”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And the girl said, "They will, in a minute."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.60,0:04:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我儿子四岁时在英国{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}When my son was four in England --{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.82,0:04:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}实际上他那会儿在哪都四岁{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Actually, he was four everywhere, to be honest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.42,0:04:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}严格地说他四岁那年在哪个国家记不清了 只记得他四岁那年{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If we're being strict about it, wherever he went, he was four that year.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.90,0:04:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}去演舞台剧《基督诞生》{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}He was in the Nativity play.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.62,0:04:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你们记得那部剧的情节吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Do you remember the story?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.57,0:04:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}应该记不得 情节太长 故事太长{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}No, it was big, it was a big story.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.22,0:04:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}梅尔.吉布森演过那部剧的续集{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Mel Gibson did the sequel,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.70,0:04:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你们也许看过 叫《基督诞生II》{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}you may have seen it. "Nativity II."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.50,0:04:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我儿子 James 在那部舞台剧里演 Joseph 我们为此很兴奋{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}But James got the part of Joseph, which we were thrilled about.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.44,0:04:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我们以为那是个主要角色{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We considered this to be one of the lead parts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.75,0:04:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我们给观众们发了T恤： 上面印着 “James Robinson 扮演 Joseph"{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We had the place crammed full of agents in T-shirts: "James Robinson IS Joseph!"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.60,0:04:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}他的角色不一定有台词 剧情是 三个国王拿着礼物走进来{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}He didn't have to speak, but you know the bit where the three kings come in?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.77,0:04:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}他们分别拿着黄金 乳香精油 没药精油{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}They come in bearing gifts, gold, frankincense and myrrh.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.82,0:04:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}演出开始了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}This really happened.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.97,0:04:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我们坐在观众席上 我认为他们应该按顺序出场{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We were sitting there and I think they just went out of sequence,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.77,0:04:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}演出结束后我们对James说： “你们刚才演的对吗”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}because we talked to the little boy afterward and we said, "You OK with that?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.57,0:04:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}他说：“对啊 怎么了 哪错了吗”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And he said, "Yeah, why? Was that wrong?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.99,0:04:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}其实他们把剧情改了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}They just switched.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.95,0:04:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}他们是这么演的：三个小演员出场{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}The three boys came in,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.42,0:05:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}四岁的小家伙们头上戴着擦杯子用的毛巾{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}four-year-olds with tea towels on their heads,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.53,0:05:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}他们放下手上拿的盒子{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and they put these boxes down,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.00,0:05:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}第一个孩子说：“我带来了黄金”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and the first boy said, "I bring you gold."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.05,0:05:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}第二个孩子说：“我带来了没药精油”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And the second boy said, "I bring you myrrh."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.83,0:05:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}第三个孩子说： “Frank带来了这个”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And the third boy said, "Frank sent this."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}以上例子的共同点就是孩子们愿意冒险{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}What these things have in common is that kids will take a chance.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.75,0:05:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}对于未知的事物 他们愿意去尝试{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If they don't know, they'll have a go.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.63,0:05:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}难道不是吗 即使尝试的结果是错误的 他们也不惧怕{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Am I right? They're not frightened of being wrong.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.84,0:05:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}当然 我并不认为错误的尝试等同于创新{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I don't mean to say that being wrong is the same thing as being creative.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.87,0:05:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但我们都知道 如果你不打算做错误的尝试{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}What we do know is, if you're not prepared to be wrong,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.07,0:05:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你永远不会创造出新东西{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}you'll never come up with anything original --{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.57,0:05:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}如果你不想让孩子们做错误的尝试{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}if you're not prepared to be wrong.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.94,0:05:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}等他们长大了 多数孩子就会丧失创新的能力{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And by the time they get to be adults, most kids have lost that capacity.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.45,0:05:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}那就会使他们也变得惧怕错误的尝试{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}They have become frightened of being wrong.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.04,0:05:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这种情况也存在于公司经营方面{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And we run our companies like this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.40,0:05:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我们不能容忍任何错误{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We stigmatize mistakes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.32,0:05:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这就使得现在的 教育体系成为 最不能容忍错误的领域{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And we're now running national education systems where mistakes are the worst thing you can make.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.62,0:06:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这样做的后果就是 我们的教育体制正在扼杀 孩子们的创造力{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And the result is that we are educating people out of their creative capacities.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.32,0:06:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}毕加索曾说过 “孩子们是天生的艺术家”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Picasso once said this, he said that all children are born artists.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.67,0:06:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}问题是我们长大后 能否继续保有艺术灵感{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}The problem is to remain an artist as we grow up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.93,0:06:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我坚信： 我们随着年龄的增长而丧失了创造力{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I believe this passionately, that we don't grow into creativity, we grow out of it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.99,0:06:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}甚至可以说 是我们所受的教育 让我们丧失了创造力{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Or rather, we get educated out of it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.32,0:06:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}为什么会这样{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}So why is this?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.82,0:06:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}五年前 我住在Stratford-on-Avon{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I lived in Stratford-on-Avon until about five years ago.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.05,0:06:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}现在我已经搬到了洛杉矶{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}In fact, we moved from Stratford to Los Angeles.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.67,0:06:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}可想而知 这是个多么合乎逻辑的移居{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}So you can imagine what a seamless transition that was.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.96,0:06:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}其实 那时我们住在 Snitterfield{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Actually, we lived in a place called Snitterfield,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.69,0:06:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}就在 Stratford 郊外 那里是 莎士比亚父亲的出生地{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}just outside Stratford, which is where Shakespeare's father was born.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.17,0:06:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你有过灵感吗 我曾经有过{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Are you struck by a new thought? I was.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.47,0:06:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你没把莎士比亚 和他的父亲联想在一起 对吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}You don't think of Shakespeare having a father, do you? Do you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.44,0:06:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}因为你忽略了 莎士比亚也曾经是个孩子 对吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Because you don't think of Shakespeare being a child, do you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.55,0:06:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}莎士比亚七岁时什么样{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Shakespeare being seven?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.67,0:06:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我从没想过{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I never thought of it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.67,0:06:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}他七岁时 的某个特定场景{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I mean, he was seven at some point.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.00,0:06:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}比如他在上 英语课 想想他在上英语课{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}He was in somebody's English class, wasn't he?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.73,0:07:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}多么不可思议{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}How annoying would that be?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.77,0:07:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}“你要努力学习”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}"Must try harder."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.57,0:07:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你能想象他父亲边说边把他抱上床{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Being sent to bed by his dad, you know, to Shakespeare,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.57,0:07:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}“现在该睡觉了” 他父亲又说{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}"Go to bed, now! And put the pencil down."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.88,0:07:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}“放下笔 别再写那些东西了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}"And stop speaking like that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.15,0:07:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS} 别人都看不懂”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG} It's confusing everybody."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.88,0:07:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}话说远了 刚才说到我们从 Stratford 搬到洛杉矶{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Anyway, we moved from Stratford to Los Angeles,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.13,0:07:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我想说的是 对于这次搬家{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and I just want to say a word about the transition.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.69,0:07:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我儿子并不愿意{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}My son didn't want to come.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.16,0:07:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我有两个孩子 儿子现在21岁了 女儿16岁{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I've got two kids; he's 21 now, my daughter's 16.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.91,0:07:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我儿子不愿搬到洛杉矶{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}He didn't want to come to Los Angeles.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.22,0:07:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}虽然他喜欢这 但在英国 他有个女友{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}He loved it, but he had a girlfriend in England.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.02,0:07:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}是他的最爱 叫 Sarah{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}This was the love of his life, Sarah.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.66,0:07:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}他们认识只有一个月后就开始交往了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}He'd known her for a month.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.55,0:08:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我们要搬家时他们已交往了4年{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Mind you, they'd had their fourth anniversary,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.22,0:08:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这对于16岁的年龄来说已经很长了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}because it's a long time when you're 16.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.41,0:08:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我儿子上了飞机后很郁闷{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}He was really upset on the plane,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.37,0:08:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}他说：“我再也找不到像 Sarah 那样的女孩了”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}he said, "I'll never find another girl like Sarah."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.80,0:08:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但说实话 做为家长的我们为此很庆幸{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And we were rather pleased about that, frankly --{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.21,0:08:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}因为{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Because {\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.11,0:08:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}那个女孩是我们搬家的主要原因{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}she was the main reason we were leaving the country.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.84,0:08:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但搬到美国后 有些事使我印象深刻 如果你周游世界{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}But something strikes you when you move to America and travel around the world:{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.20,0:08:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你会发现每个国家的教育体系 都存在相同的学科等级制度{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Every education system on Earth has the same hierarchy of subjects.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}没有例外{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Every one.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.51,0:08:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}不论哪个国家{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Doesn't matter where you go.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.28,0:08:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你认为也许会有例外 但没有{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}You'd think it would be otherwise, but it isn't.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.62,0:08:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}排在最前面的学科是数学和语言{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}At the top are mathematics and languages,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.03,0:08:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}接下去是人文学科 艺术排在最后{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}then the humanities, and at the bottom are the ar ts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.85,0:08:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}世界上所有国家都是如此{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Everywhere on Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.51,0:08:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}而且相同的还有 就是在艺术学科范围内也有等级制{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And in pretty much every system too, there's a hierarchy within the arts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.99,0:08:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}通常学校把美术课和音乐课看的较重要 然后是戏剧课和舞蹈课{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Art and music are normally given a higher status in schools than drama and dance.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.73,0:08:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}没有哪个国家的教育体系 天天安排舞蹈课{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}There isn't an education system on the planet that teaches dance everyday to children{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.95,0:08:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但却每天都安排数学课{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}the way we teach them mathematics.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.25,0:09:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}为什么 为什么不是每天安排舞蹈课呢{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Why? Why not?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.98,0:09:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我认为舞蹈课很重要{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I think this is rather important.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.58,0:09:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我认为舞蹈课和数学课同样重要{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I think math is very important, but so is dance.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.57,0:09:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}如果有允许 孩子们会不停地跳舞 我们也一样{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Children dance all the time if they're allowed to, we all do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.55,0:09:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我们都有体会 对吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We all have bodies, don't we? Did I miss a meeting?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.13,0:09:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}事实上 随着孩子年龄增长 我们开始教导他们 别的东西{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Truthfully, what happens is, as children grow up, we start to educate them progressively from the waist up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.49,0:09:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}随着他们长大 我们更关注的是他们的头脑{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And then we focus on their heads.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.86,0:09:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}而且略微偏重大脑的一侧{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And slightly to one side.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.68,0:09:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}如果你以一个外国人的身份来参观我们的教育体系{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If you were to visit education, as an alien,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.30,0:09:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}带着这样的问题：“公办教育的目的是什么”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and say "What's it for, public education?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.12,0:09:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}那么当你看到我们的教育体系产业化的发展 我相信 你就会明白{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I think you'd have to conclude, if you look at the output,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.42,0:09:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}是谁在真正从中受益 是谁被教导着该做什么不该做什么{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}who really succeeds by this, who does everything that they should,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.17,0:09:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}是谁得了满分 谁是第一名{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}who gets all the brownie points, who are the winners --{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.05,0:09:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}关于公办教育的目的 我想你会得出这样的结论{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I think you'd have to conclude the whole purpose of{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.74,0:09:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}世界上所有的公办教育 都以培养大学教授为目的{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}public education throughout the world is to produce university professors.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.61,0:09:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}难道不是吗 因为大学教授是象牙塔尖上的人{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Isn't it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.76,0:09:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我也曾是一名大学教授 也是塔尖上的人{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}They're the people who come out the top. And I used to be one, so there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.85,0:09:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我倾慕大学教授的学识{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And I like university professors,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.91,0:09:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但 我们不应该用这样一个头衔作为 衡量一个人成功与否的分水岭{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}but you know, we shouldn't hold them up as the high-water mark of all human achievement.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.90,0:10:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}其实大学教授只是360行中的一行{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}They're just a form of life, another form of life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.57,0:10:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}只不过他们比较好求知 我这样说不是因为对他们的倾慕{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}But they're rather curious, and I say this out of affection for them.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.51,0:10:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}在我看来 大学教授有个特点{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}There's something curious about professors in my experience --{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.69,0:10:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}虽然不是共性 但很典型{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}not all of them, but typically,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.60,0:10:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}他们只用脑子生活{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}they live in their heads.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.63,0:10:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}而且偏重于大脑的一侧{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}They live up there, and slightly to one side.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.28,0:10:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}用书面语来说就是 他们脑体分离{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}They're disembodied, you know, in a kind of literal way.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.74,0:10:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}他们只是把身体当作 大脑的载体而已 难道不是吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}They look upon their body as a form of transport for their heads. Don't they?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.57,0:10:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这个载体可以载着大脑去开会{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}It's a way of getting their head to meetings.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.04,0:10:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}如果你想亲身体验 你就去参加一次学术研讨会{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If you want real evidence of out-of-body experiences, get yourself along to a residential conference of senior academics,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.34,0:10:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}然后在会议结束后再去迪厅蹦迪{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and pop into the discotheque on the final night.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.55,0:10:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}在那你会看到 成年男女 在不和乐拍地疯狂摇摆{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And there, you will see it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.87,0:10:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}期待夜晚的结束好回家{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Grown men and women writhing uncontrollably, off the beat.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.97,0:11:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}写篇关于蹦迪的论文{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Waiting until it ends so they can go home and write a paper about it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.20,0:11:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}注重培养学术能力的观点根植于 我们的教育体系之中{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Our education system is predicated on the idea of academic ability.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.07,0:11:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}形成这种状况还有个原因{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And there's a reason.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.50,0:11:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}所有国家的教育体系在最初建立时 那时教育还不是公共事业{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Around the world, there were no public systems of education,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.85,0:11:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}也就是在19世纪之前{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}really, before the 19th century.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.06,0:11:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}那时建立教育体系 是为了满足工业化发展的需要{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}They all came into being to meet the needs of industrialism.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.37,0:11:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}所以有两点基本的等级原则{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}So the hierarchy is rooted on two ideas.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.69,0:11:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}第一点 对工作最实用的科目 是最重要的科目{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Number one, that the most useful subjects for work are at the top.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.17,0:11:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这样就能轻易地避开 孩子们喜欢的科目 从小就不让他们碰触{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}So you were probably steered benignly away from things at school when you were a kid,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.31,0:11:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}理由就是 不这样学就找不到工作{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}things you liked, on the grounds that you would never get a job doing that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.27,0:11:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}对吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Is that right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.49,0:11:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}别玩音乐了 你成不了音乐家；{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Don't do music, you're not going to be a musician;{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.96,0:11:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}别画画了 你成不了艺术家{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}don't do art, you won't be an artist.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.76,0:11:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这些温和的忠告 筑成现在的大错{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Benign advice -- now, profoundly mistaken.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.17,0:11:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}全世界 都被卷入了工业革命的热潮{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}The whole world is engulfed in a revolution.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.22,0:11:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}第二点 学术能力已经成为 衡量好学生的主要标准{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And the second is academic ability, which has really come to dominate our view of intelligence,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.76,0:11:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这种标准是那些大学自己制定的{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}because the universities designed the system in their image.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.09,0:11:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}只要你思考一下就会发现整个教育体系 不论哪个国家{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If you think of it, the whole system of public education around the world{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.40,0:11:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}都是一种按部就班的程序 最终目标是为了考入大学{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}is a protracted process of university entrance.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.53,0:12:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}造成的后果就是许多很有天才的 有创造力的学生被钝化了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And the consequence is that many highly-talented, brilliant, creative people think they're not,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.04,0:12:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}因为这些学生发现他们的专长在学校{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}because the thing they were good at at school wasn't valued,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.47,0:12:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}并不受重视甚至还受到蔑视{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}or was actually stigmatized.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.45,0:12:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我认为我们不能再这样扼杀孩子们的天才了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And I think we can't afford to go on that way.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.56,0:12:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}根据联合国教科文组织的统计{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}In the next 30 years, according to UNESCO,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.12,0:12:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}今后30年 全世界毕业的学生将超过 过去的总和{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}more people worldwide will be graduating through education than since the beginning of history.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.56,0:12:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这就是人口增长造成的 人口增长关系到{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}More people, and it's the combination of all the things{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.00,0:12:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我们谈论的许多话题{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}we've talked about --{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.82,0:12:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}包括技术和技术变革 对生产力的影响{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}technology and its transformation effect on work,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.75,0:12:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}人口统计学 及人口爆炸{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and demography and the huge explosion in population.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.35,0:12:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}很快 文凭就不再有含金量了{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Suddenly, degrees aren't worth anything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.10,0:12:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}是这样吧{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Isn't that true?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.81,0:12:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我上学那会儿 有文凭就有工作{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}When I was a student, if you had a degree, you had a job.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.88,0:12:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}那时候如果你没工作 那是因为你不想找{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If you didn't have a job, it's because you didn't want one.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.47,0:12:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}说实话 我那时候就是这样{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And I didn't want one, frankly.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.51,0:12:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}但现在的状况是 孩子们有文凭却经常 呆在家里打电脑游戏{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}But now kids with degrees are often heading home to carry on playing video games,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.21,0:12:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}因为以前只要学士学位的工作岗位 现在需要硕士学位{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}because you need an MA where the previous job required a BA,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.98,0:12:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}现在还没毕业的孩子将来 就得有个博士学位才好找工作{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and now you need a PhD for the other.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.26,0:12:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这就是学术学位的通货膨胀{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}It's a process of academic inflation.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.86,0:12:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这是整个教育体系 坍塌的前兆{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And it indicates the whole structure of education is shifting beneath our feet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.15,0:12:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我们必须从根本上反思 我们评价好学生的标准{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We need to radically rethink our view of intelligence.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.49,0:12:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}培养人才有三个原则{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We know three things about intelligence.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.29,0:12:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}第一 多样化{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}One, it's diverse.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.95,0:13:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我们认知世界的角度不同 有的从视觉角度{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We think about the world in all the ways that we experience it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.83,0:13:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}有的从听觉角度 有的从美学角度{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We think visually, we think in sound, we think kinesthetically.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.10,0:13:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}有的从抽象的角度 有的从动态的角度{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}We think in abstract terms, we think in movement.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.47,0:13:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}第二 好学生应该是充满活力的{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Secondly, intelligence is dynamic.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.47,0:13:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}如果观察一下人类大脑的内部组织{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If you look at the interactions of a human brain,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.03,0:13:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}就像我们 昨天所看到的演讲中演示的 大脑发育具有关联性{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}as we heard yesterday from a number of presentations, intelligence is wonderfully interactive.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.60,0:13:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}大脑不应被分成几部分{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}The brain isn't divided into compartments.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.90,0:13:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}其实我认为应该创造性地 把大脑看作一整套工序{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}In fact, creativity -- which I define as the process of having original ideas that have value --{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.40,0:13:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}生产有价值的原创想法的工序 这种原创想法往往来自互动的思考方式 而不是呆板的常规模式{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}more often than not comes about through the interaction of different disciplinary ways of seeing things.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.13,0:13:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}大脑本来就是 由神经来连接左脑和右脑 这个连接部分叫胼胝体（医学名词）{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}By the way, there's a shaft of nerves that joins the two halves of the brain called the corpus callosum.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.25,0:13:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}女性大脑中的这个部分比男性的要厚{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}It's thicker in women.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.15,0:13:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}昨天听了Helen的演讲受到启发 我认为{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Following off from Helen yesterday,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.89,0:13:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}脑部特征可能使女性更善于 应对头绪纷乱的事情 对吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}this is probably why women are better at multi-tasking. Because you are, aren't you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.15,0:13:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}虽然关于这方面的研究有很多 但我对于这方面的了解{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}There's a raft of research, but I know it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.12,0:13:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}其实来源于我的亲身体验{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}from my personal life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.85,0:13:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我妻子在家做饭时 感谢上帝 她不常做饭{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If my wife is cooking a meal at home -- which is not often, thankfully.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.02,0:14:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}虽然她不擅厨艺但很擅长其他一些事{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}No, she's good at some things,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.20,0:14:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}不过她做饭时总是 打打电话{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}but if she's cooking, she's dealing with people on the phone,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.85,0:14:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}和孩子们说说话 给天棚刷刷漆{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}she's talking to the kids, she's painting the ceiling,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.91,0:14:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}还在旁边做开胸手术{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}she's doing open-heart surgery over here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.03,0:14:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}而我做饭时就会关上厨房门{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}If I'm cooking, the door is shut,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.01,0:14:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}不让孩子们进来打扰 不打电话{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}the kids are out, the phone's on the hook,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.38,0:14:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}这时如果我妻子进来我会很生气{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}if she comes in I get annoyed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.17,0:14:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我会这样对我妻子说： “Terry 我在煎鸡蛋 请你别打扰” {\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I say, "Terry, please, I'm trying to fry an egg in here. Give me a break." {\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.32,0:14:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}大家都知道那句有哲理的话{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Actually, do you know that old philosophical thing,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.05,0:14:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}如果森林里有棵树倒了可没人听到 那是否意味着没发生过{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}if a tree falls in a forest and nobody hears it, did it happen?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.12,0:14:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}记得这句话吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Remember that old chestnut?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.59,0:14:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}最近我看到一件很棒的T恤 上面印着：{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I saw a great t-shirt recently, which said,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.02,0:14:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}“如果一个男人说出他的心声 却是在森林里说的{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}"If a man speaks his mind in a forest,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.62,0:14:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}而且没被女人听到 那应该不算犯错吧”{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}and no woman hears him, is he still wrong?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.14,0:14:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}培养好学生的第三个原则就是 个性化{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}And the third thing about intelligence is, it's distinct.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.15,0:14:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我目前在写本书 书名叫《顿悟》{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I'm doing a new book at the moment called "Epiphany,"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.30,0:15:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}素材来自一些 访谈 访谈内容是关于怎样发现 自身的才能{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}which is based on a series of interviews with people about how they discovered their talent.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.19,0:15:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}对于这点我很感兴趣{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I'm fascinated by how people got to be there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.49,0:15:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}激发我写这本书的原因是一次对话{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}It's really prompted by a conversation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.67,0:15:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}我采访了一位很优秀的女士 也许很多人没听说过这个人{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}I had with a wonderful woman who maybe most people have never heard of,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.17,0:15:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}她叫Gillian Lynne,{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Gillian Lynne.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.93,0:15:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}你们知道这个人吗{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Have you heard of her?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.35,0:15:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}应该有人知道吧{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}Some have.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.30,0:15:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rYYeTS-CHS}她是一个舞蹈编剧 所有人都知道她的作品{\r}\N{\rYYeTS-ENG}She's a choreographer, and everybody knows her work.{\r}
